The paper presents a method for learning Bayesian Networks using informative prior beliefs, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The prior beliefs are based on knowledge about causal and associative relations between variables, which is related to the field of causal inference and structure learning (cs.SI). The paper also proposes a novel search-operator, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and search algorithms (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses experiments and results, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
